{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_1kahlo_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280602024/1937100301/0722.xml":{"full_text":"Large Backlogs Assure Ac\ntive Operations for Rest\nof Year.\nBs the Associated Press.\nNEW YORK, October 2.\u2014In con-\ntrast with the prospects of domestic\nair transport lines, the business outlook\nfor airplane manufacturers continues\nto be quite favorable and, according\nto a survey of the industry by Standard\nStatistics Co., no interruption of the\nupward trend in earnings appears in\nprospect for 1938.\nA marked increase in traffic which\ndeveloped in the third quarter is\nunderstood to have restored operations\nof major transport lines to a profitable\nbasis and third quarter earnings should\noffset, a substantial part of the first\nhalf deficit, the survey indicated.\nAs to the manufacturing companies,\nthe large amount of unfilled orders,\nwhich Standard estimated at around\n$125,000,000 for the larger companies\nincluded in its survey, assures main\ntenance of a high rate of operations\nfor the rest of the year.\nIncluded in this backlog are sub\nstantial new orders placed by the Gov\nernment with such concerns as Boeing,\nCurtiss-Wright. Douglas, United Air\ncraft and the manufacturing division\nOf North American Aviation.\nDouglas Aircraft, according to the\nsurvey, continues to have the largest\nbacklog, close to S34.000.000. while\nUnited and Curtiss-Wright are be\nlieved to have unfilled orders of\n$25 000.000 and $20,000,000. respec\ntively.\n\u2022'Continuance of the unsettled foreign\npolitical situation and the consequent\nrace to build up armaments promise to\nmaintain export sales at high levels\nfor an extended period, provided the\nGovernment places no important re\nstrictions on sales abroad,'\u2019 the survey\nContinues, adding:\n\"The higher profit ratio available on\nmost export contracts makes this busi\nness highly important to domestic\nproducers.\u201d\nACACIA HEAD SEES\nSOUND RECOVERY\nWilliam Montgomery Believes All\nEssential Factors Available\nfor Rapid Progress.\nEconomic conditions in the United\nStates are fundamentally sound and\nthere are available all factors essential\nto a period of unusual growth and\nprogress. William Montgomery. Presi\ndent of the Acacia Mutual Life Insur\nance Co., said yesterday on his return\nfrom a trip to the South, Middle West\nand Pacific Coast.\n\"With respect to the life insurance\ncompanies, they are experiencing one\nof the best years in their history. Al\nmost without exception the companies\nare bettering last year's marks all\nalong the line. Total insurance in\nforce, total new business written, and\ntotal assets all are at peak levels,\" he\nreported.\nUpon his return yesterday, Mr.\nMontgomery was presented with a\nscroll upon which were inscribed the\nnames of members of the home office\nstaff who took part in a unique testi\nmonial campaign which resulted in\ntheir paying for policies on their own\nlives to a total of $642,200 of insur\nance.\n\nF. S. C. C. FIXES PRICES\nFOR APPLE PURCHASES\nMARTINSBURG. W Va\u201e October 2\n(Special).\u2014The Federal Surplus Com\nmodities Corporation, now buying ap\nples in this producing belt both to\nhelp stimulate the market and provide\napples for relief roll families, an\nnounced today it would pay the fol\nlowing on York Imperial stock, pick\ning of which is just ahead: Utility\ngrade 2\u20192 inches up baskets fifty\ncents: Utility 2'j inches up in bulk\nsixty cents hundred weight: Combina\ntion United States 1-Utility 2'2 up\nbaskets sixty cents: Combination\nUnited States 1-Utility 2'-_. inches up\nbulk seventy cents hundredweight.\nThe F. S. C. C. has been paying the\nfollowing scale for Stayman stock,\npicking of which is now in progress:\nUnited States Utility 2'2 inches and\nup in baskets sixty cents. There was\nho quotation for bulk Stayman stock.\nBANK STOCKS RISE.\nNEW YORK. October 2 (/P).\u2014 New\nYork City bank stocks showed a broad\nrecovery this week, according to Hoit,\nRose Troster. bank stock dealers.\nAggregate market value of 16 leading\nissues on October 1 amounted to\n$1,680,131,000 against $1,602,489,000\non September 24, an increase of 4.85\nper cent.\nLOST.\nBANKBOOK, containing $85 cash. $73\nchecks, between 15th and N. Y. and Provi\nrlmre Hospital; reward Georgia nliis.\nBOSTON BULL TERRIER, sick Saturday1\nIror IS04 Forest Glen rd.. Forest Glen.\nMd. Belriender kindly call Shepherd\nS4!\u00bb0-J._evenlngs._\nCOLLIE DOG. answers to 'Lassie*'; yel\njon and white. _ Worth 4678-M\nCRESCENT-AND-STAR TIE PIN with small\ndiamonds, vicinity !\u00bbth and Monroe sts. n.e.\n1 Liberal reward. Mr. Stewart. 3901 J2th\nst._n p._Nort h_2333._\nFOX TERRIER PUPPY; male: white with\nforovkn and black, face and ears: 2 black\nspots on back. Answers to \"Skippy.\u201d Tag\nNo. 19447 Reward. Dec 02514.\nGERMAN POLICE DOG collar with doe s\nname and owner's. Call Adams 8352.\nReward _\nGOLD BROOCH, largrfl antique, some time\nbet. Sept. 1 and Sept. 17. Lincoln 3817.\nLiberal reward;____3* _\nPOCKETBOOK. black: left on Brookland\ncar about 4:30 Sat.. 18th and Pa. Val\nuable papers, money; liberal reward. Call\nWest oiG 5._\nPOCKETBOOK. containing Army discharge\nand American Legion card. James Arcaro.\n4113 13th st. n.w. Adams T832-J._\nPOLICE DOG. female, dark brown, white\nmarkings, strayed from 37th st.. Mt.\nRainier with chain and tan collar Phone\nNational 5087 or Greenwood 1717. Re\nward;_\nROWBOAT frem Eastern Power Boat Club.\n14th and N s.e.. Tues.. 11 ft., grav inside\nand out. rope around gunnel. Reward.\nLincoln 3542: West 3102._3*\nWRIST WATCH: gold. Tiffany; initials on\nback. M. J. T. sapphire in stem: lost\nbetween Carlton Hotel and Stoneleigh\nCourt Saturday morning: reward if re\nturned to Carlton Hotel. M. J. Todd\nSUM OF MONEY ill envelope with greeting\ncard: vicinity N. Capitol. N. J. ave.. Eye st.:\nreward._National 3832._>\u00bb\nFRIDAY. Oct. 2. black leather key ease.\ncontaining several keys: initials T. L. H.\nFinder pleas